Cutting edge...yea... :P
@Quantumworld: Seems that this card is also used for wifi pentesting. I would imagine things should go smoothly....should. ;)

@Wraith: For switching from one pc to another, I ZIP'd the data directory within /ZeroBundle/ZeroNet. After that, I unzip it and place data folder into /ZeroBundle/ZeroNet on new computer. After that, start ZeroNet and it worked for me. Granted, this is on *nix. YRMV
@Quantumworld: After receiving the card, it appears 5GHz is not doing well and just disconnects. 2.4GHz has been solid and not dropping out. Not sure if it's a range thing? Only ~7 meters away.
